nirojsapkota:
Sorry for the late reply. But i encountered same problem yesterday. The reason for the error is , while drawing the bars in morris.js. it calculates the width of each bar to be drawn by taking the value of Dom element width( where graph is to be drawn) and the size of data. So if the data is large then the width of the bar becomes negative (which morris should have taken care of ) and raphael.js throws exception while trying to set the width of rect to -ve value. 
For the solution, i added some handling when the width comes negative. Here i calculated the data size that can be fitted within the given dom width by keeping the bar width of 0.5 and removed the additional data. My piece of code is added in the method Bar.prototype.drawSeries = function() {} 

```
/*Fix for negative bar width, trimming the data and calculating the fitting data length and setting bar of size 0.5 */
    if(barWidth <0){
        var fit_data_length = Math.floor(this.width * this.options.barSizeRatio/(numBars*0.5 + this.options.barGap * (numBars-1)));
        //data removed from tail
        this.options.data.splice(fit_data_length);
        barWidth=0.5;}
```
